@OmegaSerris:  

That wouldn't fly in a tournament at all. Or in a lot of play groups.  

It doesn't say "half of their library", it says "the **TOP** half of their library". That's very important due to topdeck manipulation effects, and spells/effects that put cards on the bottom of libraries. If you played something like [Long-Term Plans](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Long-Term Plans), [Enigma Sphinx](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enigma Sphinx) or [Worldly Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Worldly Tutor), I want to be damn sure that card is in your graveyard. Your method gives a 50/50 chance of it still being in the library. Same applies to if I played [Condemn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Condemn) on your [Anger](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Anger) or [Brawn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brawn). I want to make sure that card is on the bottom of your library, not in your graveyard.

